  "status": "Final",
  "summary": "This standard defines a registry where smart contracts and regular accounts can publish which functionality they implement---either directly or through a proxy contract. Anyone can query this registry to ask if a specific address implements a given interface and which smart contract handles its implementation. This registry MAY be deployed on any chain and shares the same address on all chains. Interfaces with zeroes (`0`) as the last 28 bytes are considered [ERC-165] interfaces, and this registry SHALL forward the call to the contract to see if it implements the interface. This contract also acts as an [ERC-165] cache to reduce gas consumption.",
  "title": "Pseudo-introspection Registry Contract"
}